                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.294,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I have filed an opinion responding essentially to Justice Breyer\u0027s proposal that we abolish the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 10.294,
                                "stop": 14.134,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I will not burden you with that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.134,
                                "stop": 24.483,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Last Friday five Justices took the issue of same-sex marriage away from the people, on the basis of nothing but their own policy preferences."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.483,
                                "stop": 50.119,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Today two Justices announced their intention to have done with this Court\u0027s 30 year practice of merely placing unrealistic obstacles in the path of capital punishment; you heard some of them discussed in the majority opinion today, to have done with that policy and now just honestly abolish it entirely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.119,
                                "stop": 59.439,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As it happens, unlike opposite sex marriage, the death penalty is approved by the Constitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.439,
                                "stop": 61.782,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "You are all familiar with the provision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.782,
                                "stop": 69.349,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "No person shall be deprived of life, liberty, or property without due process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.349,
                                "stop": 80.394,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Another provision requires a grand jury indictment for all capital crimes; that is all crimes involving the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.394,
                                "stop": 94.025,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Nonetheless, these two Justices now propose to take the issue of capital punishment entirely away from the people on the basis of nothing but their own policy preferences."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.025,
                                "stop": 101.6,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I find two of their arguments particularly wryly amusing; one is the 18 year delay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.6,
                                "stop": 114.158,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The 18 year delay is the product of the unrealistic impediments this Court has imposed to imposition of the death penalty over the past 30 years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.158,
                                "stop": 121.114,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And the fact that 19 states have abolished the death penalty is also largely attributable to the same thing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 121.114,
                                "stop": 126.267,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is so expensive and it takes so long to impose the death penalty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.267,
                                "stop": 139.717,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Maybe we should celebrate the fact that two Justices are willing to kill the death penalty outright instead of pecking it to death, as has been the case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.717,
                                "stop": 147.648,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is not often in the law that so few have so quickly changed so much."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
